# EAS build ignore list. Mirrors .gitignore EXACTLY, with ONE deliberate difference: the
# `google-services.json` lines are omitted so `frontend/google-services.json` is INCLUDED in the
# `eas build --local` tarball. app.config.ts's `googleServicesFile` (from GOOGLE_SERVICES_JSON) then
# has a file to copy during prebuild, so the google-services Gradle plugin injects the Firebase
# resources — without them the app crashes on launch ("Default FirebaseApp is not initialized") and
# `getDevicePushTokenAsync()` throws, leaving the approval-push FCM token unregistered.
# google-services.json is a per-app CLIENT config that already ships inside every APK; it is not a
# private secret, and git still ignores it so it is never committed.
node_modules/
dist/
*.log
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
stewra.env
.mailcredentials
**/.mailcredentials
.DS_Store
coverage/
.next/
*.tsbuildinfo

.claude/hooks/.session-skills/
.apptest
.claude/tsc-cache/

/frontend/android/
/frontend/ios/
.expo/
**/.expo/
/frontend/build-*.apk
/frontend/build-*.aab
/frontend/build/
